Properkeys Limited, is a property sourcing company. We source off-market properties for our clients (“buyers”). When someone contacts Properkeys, they may want to know how they may go about getting registered with our company, or possibly what properties we may have in stock. Maybe, a landlord contacts us wanting to list his property on our website. Our process goes as follows:
1.	Upon initial engagement with our prospect, we schedule (either by phone or via the website) a 15min call. The purpose of this call is to discuss what requirements they have when searching for a property.
2.	We capture our prospect’s requirements in our CRM database. Once the call is ended, we send them an email summarising their requirements with a copy of our contract.
3.	The client must return a signed copy of this contract to info@properkeys.co.uk in order for Properkeys to begin their search
a.	By signing the contract, our now client gives permission for Properkeys to carry out a bespoke search on their behalf. By signing the contract, Properkeys is saying we are committed to putting in the time and effort into finding them the right property
4.	If they express the need for an accountant, broker or solicitor, we will send them a separate email referring them to one of our partners
5.	Once the signed contract is received, we begin their bespoke property search. We are bargain hunters, so we will always search for the best possible deals. More importantly, deals that meet all their requirements!
6.	We aim to find our client a property in the quickest time possible. After we have sourced the property, we stack the deal and present to them the numbers. If they are happy with the offer, they will pay 20% of the finder’s fee to hold the property. Once they’ve viewed the property, if they are satisfied, they will pay the remainder of that finder’s fee, ultimately closing the deal.
